          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the crème pâtissière",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk the {{egg-yolks}}, {{caster-sugar}}, and {{cornflour}} together. Heat the {{whole-milk}} until steaming and pour slowly over the egg mixture, whisking constantly. Return to the pan and cook over medium heat, stirring, until thick and bubbling. Cook for 2 more minutes. Stir in the {{vanilla-extract}}. Press cling film onto the surface and refrigerate until cold.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape the pastry",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 200°C fan. Cut the {{puff-pastry}} into 8 squares, roughly 12 × 12 cm. See the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "Danish parcel shaping",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpa2djuv0000ugv4u0r7wb1s"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " note. Arrange on lined baking trays. Chill for 15 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fill, top, and bake 20 to 25 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spoon a tablespoon of cold crème pâtissière into the centre of each pastry. Fan 4 to 5 slices of {{apple-eating}} over the custard. Brush the pastry borders with beaten {{eggs}}. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until the pastry is deep gold and the apple edges are beginning to caramelise. Warm the {{apricot-jam}} with a splash of water, sieve, and brush over the apples while hot.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
